eir nexus remains unsurpassed as a point of reference for contemporary thought itself.Key FeaturesThe first book to examine Lacan, Deleuze and Badiou togetherReconstructs a fundamental conceptual history of Badiou, Deleuze and Lacan's influences and intellectual contextIdentifies and examines the key themes in contemporary European thought: the event, time and truthShows how Deleuze and Badiou have followed and contravened the Lacanian intervention without reverting to pre-Lacanian positions"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPhilosophy, Frenchy20th century. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aClemens, Justin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRoffe, Jon, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078045140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748682065zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748682065423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748682065/original  a978-3-11-078045-1  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK